The language of the Primate in his letters seems to leave no doubt that the sentence had been issued ;⁶ but the Commissioners, after seeing the official documenta of the Court of Canterbury, and learning what had passed at Orvieto and Monte Fiascone, decided that he was not actually excommuni- cate at his death.
